{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "conservative_regrid_overlap_join",
    "description": "M4 END-TO-END worked example (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §A.8 / §8.1 / §6.1; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.8; bead ess-my4.4.5): the FULL conservative-regridding overlap-join idiom in one document — the synthesis the schema-only blocker fixtures (bin_skolem_spatial_join.esm = broad phase, intersect_polygon_clip_area.esm = narrow phase) deferred here. The operation is `F_tgt[j] = (1/A_j)·Σ_i A_ij·F_src[i]`, `A_ij = area(src_i ∩ tgt_j)`, `A_j = Σ_i A_ij` — verified piece-by-piece against ConservativeRegridding.jl / EarthSciData.jl (§A.8). The A.8 mapping, in the order the equations realize it: (1) OVERLAP PAIRS {(i,j):A_ij>0} — NOT M2's equi-only join.on directly (the spatial/theta join), realized as a bin-Skolem EQUI-join: each cell's representative bbox corner is quantized to an INTEGER lat-lon bin via `floor` (the item-3 decision — no new bin/floor leaf op), a bin key is minted with `skolem`, and the candidate pairs are the landed M2 `join.on` of source and target cells sharing a bin key (a `distinct` bool_and_or index-set-producing aggregate, id `candidate_set`, materialized as the derived `candidate_pairs` set). Integer bin keys keep this candidate set BYTE-IDENTICAL across bindings (§5.8.5 / §5.5 determinism — no floating-point coordinate comparison enters the broad phase; the sorted total order of §5.7 fixes the emitted set); the adversarial permuted-input-order variant collapsing to the identical candidate set is asserted by the M4 conformance gate (ess-my4.4.8 / §5.8.6). STR-tree acceleration is an explicit perf follow-on (a physical-operator/planner concern), NOT in scope and NOT in the IR. (2) A_ij — the `intersect_polygon` kernel leaf + the `polygon_area` `sum_product` FAQ (§8.1): the narrow phase, demonstrated here on a representative candidate pair (the `clip`/`A_ij_rep` observed pair, mirroring intersect_polygon_clip_area.esm) and supplied to the assembly as the build-once sparse overlap-area FACTOR `A_ij` (ConservativeRegridding.jl's `intersections` matrix of RAW areas — the static-partition build-once output, §6.1; one clip per candidate pair fills each entry, exactly as `dc`/`dv` are factors over the derived edge set in edge_enumeration_area_eff.esm). ZERO-AREA FILTERING: a candidate that clips to a sub-`atol` sliver is treated as equal-to-zero (§5.8.2) and dropped from the surviving-overlap set via `filter: A_ij > atol` on the assembly aggregates — this is exactly §5.8.5's 'candidate set ≠ surviving-overlap set' boundary made explicit: the join produces the byte-identical CANDIDATE set, the filter produces the tolerance-dependent SURVIVING set. (3) A_j = Σ_i A_ij — the group-by-`j` `sum_product` FAQ (ConservativeRegridding.jl's row-sums → `dst_areas`). (4) APPLY Σ_i A_ij·F_src[i] — a `sum_product` FAQ over the overlap set (the sparse mat-vec `mul!(dst, intersections, src)`); dynamic if F_src is time-varying (§6.1). (5) NORMALIZE /A_j — elementwise, foldable to build time (`dst ./= dst_areas`); partition-of-unity Σ_i W_ij = 1 holds BY CONSTRUCTION because the denominator is the row-sum of the SAME computed areas (§5.8.3). The `mass_tgt` tracer integrates Σ_j A_j·F_tgt[j], the conserved global mass (§5.8.3 conservation invariant). NO NEW PHYSICAL OPERATOR: the idiom composes from `floor`, `skolem`, `join.on`, `distinct`, `sum_product`, and the already-landed `intersect_polygon` leaf. STRUCTURAL fixture: validates against the additive M3+M4 schema with no evaluator (skolem/distinct/intersect_polygon are resolver/kernel concerns — the value-invention half rides the M3 determinism goldens, the clip is the tolerance-based M4 kernel gate ess-my4.4.8, and the per-binding assembly is ess-my4.4.6/.7/.12).",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.slit"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "geometry",
      "conservative-regridding",
      "overlap-join",
      "bin-skolem",
      "spatial-join",
      "floor",
      "skolem",
      "join",
      "intersect_polygon",
      "polygon-area",
      "value-invention",
      "partition-of-unity",
      "conservation",
      "end-to-end",
      "conformance",
      "schema",
      "ess-my4.4.5"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "ConservativeRegridOverlapJoin": {
      "index_sets": {
        "coord": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 2
        },
        "cell_verts": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 4
        },
        "src_cells": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 3
        },
        "tgt_cells": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 3
        },
        "candidate_pairs": {
          "kind": "derived",
          "from_faq": "candidate_set"
        },
        "clip_ring": {
          "kind": "derived",
          "from_faq": "overlap_clip"
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "src_lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "Source-cell representative longitude (e.g. the bbox-min corner). A float coordinate that enters ONLY the integer binning via `floor`, never a raw join comparison (§5.8.5)."
        },
        "src_lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "Source-cell representative latitude — the other binning coordinate."
        },
        "tgt_lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Target-cell representative longitude."
        },
        "tgt_lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Target-cell representative latitude."
        },
        "dx": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Bin width in degrees — the exactly-defined integer quantization step of the broad phase (§5.8.5). Shared by source and target so a common bin key means the bboxes fall in the same bucket."
        },
        "dy": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Bin height in degrees."
        },
        "atol": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Sliver floor (§5.8.2): an overlap area at or below `atol` (≈ 1e-15·R²) is treated as equal-to-zero — 'present-but-tiny' and 'absent' both collapse to no contribution. It is the threshold of the zero-area `filter` that turns the byte-identical CANDIDATE set into the tolerance-dependent SURVIVING-overlap set (§5.8.5)."
        },
        "src_poly_rep": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["cell_verts", "coord"],
          "description": "A representative source cell as a closed lon-lat vertex ring (src_poly_rep[v,1]=lon, src_poly_rep[v,2]=lat) — the `poly_a` operand of the narrow-phase clip demo below. An ordinary [verts, coord] coordinate array (no bespoke polygon type, §8.1). In the full mesh there is one such ring per source cell; the clip runs once per candidate pair to fill each `A_ij` entry."
        },
        "tgt_poly_rep": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["cell_verts", "coord"],
          "description": "A representative target cell ring — the `poly_b` operand of the clip demo."
        },
        "A_ij": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells", "tgt_cells"],
          "description": "The build-once sparse overlap-area matrix A_ij = polygon_area(intersect_polygon(src_i, tgt_j)) — ConservativeRegridding.jl's `intersections` matrix of RAW areas, the static-partition (§6.1) NARROW-phase output that the assembly consumes as a factor (analogous to `dc`/`dv` over the derived edge set in edge_enumeration_area_eff.esm). Entries for non-candidate (different-bin) pairs are 0 — those (i,j) never enter the bin-Skolem join — and sub-`atol` sliver entries are 0 by the §5.8.2 snapping; both are excluded by the join + zero-area `filter` of the assembly aggregates. Its per-pair provenance is the `clip`/`A_ij_rep` demo and intersect_polygon_clip_area.esm; cross-binding A_ij agreement is tolerance-based (§5.8.2), gated by ess-my4.4.8."
        },
        "F_src": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "The source field being remapped. A `parameter` here (static field, build-once apply); in the time-varying case it is `state`/`discrete` and the apply FAQ (eq. 5) becomes CONTINUOUS-cadence per §6.1 — the build-once weights / apply-many split is exactly the static/dynamic partition."
        },
        "src_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each source cell: skolem(\"bin\", floor(lon/dx), floor(lat/dy)). `floor` does the integer quantization (no bespoke binning op); `skolem` mints the content-addressed key. The equi-join column the candidate set joins on."
        },
        "tgt_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each target cell — identically quantized, so a shared key means source and target bboxes fall in the same broad-phase bucket."
        },
        "pair_exists": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["candidate_pairs"],
          "description": "Membership over the candidate overlap-pair set produced by the bin-Skolem equi-join (the broad phase) — the byte-identical integer candidate set of §5.8.5, materialized as the derived `candidate_pairs` index set via from_faq:\"candidate_set\"."
        },
        "clip": {
          "type": "observed",
          "shape": ["clip_ring", "coord"],
          "description": "NARROW-PHASE DEMO: the clipped overlap ring A ∩ B for a representative candidate pair — the `intersect_polygon` leaf output, a vertex ring of DATA-DEPENDENT length whose vertex set is the derived `clip_ring` index set (from_faq:\"overlap_clip\", riding the M3 value-invention machinery, §8.1). One such clip is computed per candidate pair to fill the `A_ij` factor.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "intersect_polygon",
            "id": "overlap_clip",
            "manifold": "spherical",
            "args": ["src_poly_rep", "tgt_poly_rep"]
          }
        },
        "A_ij_rep": {
          "type": "observed",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "NARROW-PHASE DEMO: the representative overlap area A_ij = polygon_area(clip) — an ORDINARY sum_product FAQ over the clipped ring (NOT a new op; the body is the illustrative cross-term over ring vertices, the exact planar-shoelace / spherical-excess integrand is the evaluator kernel's, ess-my4.4.3/.4/.11). This is how each entry of the build-once `A_ij` factor is produced.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": [],
            "ranges": {
              "v": { "from": "clip_ring" }
            },
            "args": ["clip"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                0.5,
                { "op": "index", "args": ["clip", "v", 1] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["clip", "v", 2] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        "A_j": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Target-cell area denominator A_j = Σ_i A_ij — the group-by-`j` row-sum of the overlap-area matrix (ConservativeRegridding.jl's `dst_areas`). Because the SAME computed areas feed both the apply numerator and this denominator, the partition-of-unity Σ_i W_ij = 1 is exact by construction (§5.8.3) regardless of edge-model error."
        },
        "F_tgt": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "The regridded field F_tgt[j] = (1/A_j)·Σ_i A_ij·F_src[i] = Σ_i W_ij·F_src[i] with W_ij = A_ij/A_j — the apply FAQ (sparse mat-vec) followed by the elementwise normalize (`dst ./= dst_areas`)."
        },
        "mass_tgt": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Conservation tracer: integrates the global remapped mass-rate Σ_j A_j·F_tgt[j]. Equals Σ_i A_i·F_src[i] when cell areas are exact (§5.8.3 conservation invariant) — the well-formed ODE that consumes the regridding output and exercises the conservation gate."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "(1a) OVERLAP PAIRS — bin each SOURCE cell to an integer lat-lon bin key. floor(lon/dx), floor(lat/dy) are integer bin coordinates (the existing `floor` op); skolem mints the content-addressed bin key. Per-element map (output i, no contraction).",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["src_bin", "i"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": { "from": "src_cells" } },
            "args": ["src_lon", "src_lat", "dx", "dy"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["src_lon", "i"] }, "dx"] }] },
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["src_lat", "i"] }, "dy"] }] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(1b) OVERLAP PAIRS — bin each TARGET cell identically (same dx/dy quantization).",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["tgt_bin", "j"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" } },
            "args": ["tgt_lon", "tgt_lat", "dx", "dy"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["tgt_lon", "j"] }, "dx"] }] },
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["tgt_lat", "j"] }, "dy"] }] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(1c) OVERLAP PAIRS — the candidate overlap-pair set = the bin-Skolem EQUI-join. The index-set-producing aggregate (bool_and_or, distinct:true, id `candidate_set` referenced by candidate_pairs.from_faq) ranges source i and target j, the M2 `join.on` keeps only (i,j) whose bin keys are EQUAL, and skolem(\"pair\", i, j) names each surviving candidate; the `true` body marks membership. Integer bin keys ⇒ the candidate set is byte-identical across bindings in the §5.7 sorted order (§5.8.5). No spatial-index op in the IR — the index is a physical-operator concern (STR-tree acceleration is the perf follow-on, out of scope).",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["pair_exists", "p"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "id": "candidate_set",
            "semiring": "bool_and_or",
            "distinct": true,
            "output_idx": ["p"],
            "ranges": {
              "i": { "from": "src_cells" },
              "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" }
            },
            "join": [
              { "on": [["src_bin", "tgt_bin"]] }
            ],
            "args": ["src_bin", "tgt_bin"],
            "key": { "op": "skolem", "args": ["pair", "i", "j"] },
            "expr": { "op": "true", "args": [] }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(3) A_j = Σ_i A_ij — the group-by-`j` sum_product FAQ (ConservativeRegridding.jl's row-sums → dst_areas). Ranges source i and target j; the `join.on` restricts the contraction to the bin-Skolem CANDIDATE pairs (broad phase); the `filter: A_ij > atol` drops sub-atol slivers → the SURVIVING-overlap set (§5.8.5 candidate≠surviving; zero-area filtering). output_idx [j] keeps the target index and contracts i. The denominator that makes the weights a partition of unity by construction (§5.8.3).",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["A_j", "j"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": {
              "i": { "from": "src_cells" },
              "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" }
            },
            "join": [
              { "on": [["src_bin", "tgt_bin"]] }
            ],
            "filter": {
              "op": ">",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["A_ij", "i", "j"] }, "atol"]
            },
            "args": ["A_ij", "src_bin", "tgt_bin"],
            "expr": { "op": "index", "args": ["A_ij", "i", "j"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(4)+(5) APPLY + NORMALIZE — F_tgt[j] = (1/A_j[j]) · Σ_i A_ij·F_src[i]. The inner sum_product FAQ over the overlap set is the sparse mat-vec `mul!(dst, intersections, src)` (same bin-Skolem candidate join + zero-area filter as A_j); the elementwise `1/A_j[j]` factor outside it is the normalize `dst ./= dst_areas` (NORMALIZE, foldable to build time). Together: F_tgt = Σ_i W_ij·F_src[i], W_ij = A_ij/A_j, Σ_i W_ij = 1 by construction.",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["F_tgt", "j"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              { "op": "/", "args": [1.0, { "op": "index", "args": ["A_j", "j"] }] },
              {
                "op": "aggregate",
                "semiring": "sum_product",
                "output_idx": ["j"],
                "ranges": {
                  "i": { "from": "src_cells" },
                  "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" }
                },
                "join": [
                  { "on": [["src_bin", "tgt_bin"]] }
                ],
                "filter": {
                  "op": ">",
                  "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["A_ij", "i", "j"] }, "atol"]
                },
                "args": ["A_ij", "F_src", "src_bin", "tgt_bin"],
                "expr": {
                  "op": "*",
                  "args": [
                    { "op": "index", "args": ["A_ij", "i", "j"] },
                    { "op": "index", "args": ["F_src", "i"] }
                  ]
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "Conservation tracer: d(mass_tgt)/dt = Σ_j A_j[j]·F_tgt[j], the global remapped mass-rate. A well-formed ODE that consumes the regridding output; equals Σ_i A_i·F_src[i] when areas are exact (§5.8.3 conservation invariant).",
          "lhs": { "op": "D", "args": ["mass_tgt"], "wrt": "t" },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": [],
            "ranges": { "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" } },
            "args": ["A_j", "F_tgt"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["A_j", "j"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["F_tgt", "j"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
